According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global rice flour market was valued at USD 12.91 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 13.27 billion in 2025 to USD 15.71 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 2.9% during the forecast period. Increasing consumer awareness of gluten intolerance, rising demand for healthy food alternatives, and the growing popularity of Asian cuisine are key factors driving market growth worldwide.
Rice flour, produced by finely milling rice grains, has become a preferred gluten-free alternative to wheat flour due to its excellent baking properties, digestibility, and versatility. It is widely used in rice noodles, bakery products, desserts, snacks, sauces, and as a thickening agent in refrigerated and frozen foods. Beyond the food industry, rice flour is also finding growing applications in pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.
